The paper focuses on the problem of performing random walks efficiently in a distributed network, which is a topic related to distributed computing (cs.DC) and distributed systems (cs.DS). The paper also presents algorithms for computing a random spanning tree and estimating mixing time, which are topics related to network science (cs.SI) and network infrastructure (cs.NI). Finally, the paper discusses lower bounds and algorithmic complexity, which are topics related to algorithms (cs.AL).
